<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17640502-44">
               <interp inst="t17640502-44" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17640502-44" type="year" value="1764"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17640502-44" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17640502"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17640502-44" type="date" value="17640502"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17640502-44-off244-c280" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640502-44-defend360 t17640502-44-off244 t17640502-44-verdict248"></join>
         
               <p>271. (L.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17640502-44-defend360" type="defendantName">
                     Michael 
                     Levi 
                  <interp inst="t17640502-44-defend360" type="surname" value="Levi"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-44-defend360" type="given" value="Michael"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-44-defend360" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t17640502-44-off244" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17640502-44-off244" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-44-off244" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing four pieces of velvet, being part of a man's coat, value 14 s. six pieces of flowered silk, being part of a woman's gown, value 10 s.
            </rs> the property of 
               <persName id="t17640502-44-victim361" type="victimName">
                  Lazarus 
                  Barnard 
               <interp inst="t17640502-44-victim361" type="surname" value="Barnard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-44-victim361" type="given" value="Lazarus"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-44-victim361" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640502-44-off244 t17640502-44-victim361"></join>
                  </persName>
             , <rs id="t17640502-44-cd245" type="crimeDate">March 15</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640502-44-off244 t17640502-44-cd245"></join>. +</p>
               <p>Lazarus Barnard, being a <rs id="t17640502-44-viclabel246" type="occupation">Polish Jew</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640502-44-victim361 t17640502-44-viclabel246"></join>, and speaking the Hebrew language, 
               <persName id="t17640502-44-person362">
                  Samuel 
                  Jacobs 
               <interp inst="t17640502-44-person362" type="surname" value="Jacobs"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-44-person362" type="given" value="Samuel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-44-person362" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             was sworn interpreter.</p>
               <p>Lazarus Barnard. I am a Polish Jew. I hired the prisoner as a <rs id="t17640502-44-deflabel247" type="occupation">porter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640502-44-defend360 t17640502-44-deflabel247"></join>, to carry these things, with others, in a bundle, to a warehouse, and paid him; and when I came to look over my goods, these were missing. He carried them from Wapping to St. James's, Duke's Place. When I came to make my complaint to my countrymen, and another man, they told me they had seen the prisoner with these same goods; four pieces of cut velvet, and six pieces of stuff for a gown. I sent my countryman, 
               <persName id="t17640502-44-person363">
                  Levi 
                  Joseph 
               <interp inst="t17640502-44-person363" type="surname" value="Joseph"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-44-person363" type="given" value="Levi"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-44-person363" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , to whom the prisoner had offered them to sale, as he told me, to buy them again of the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17640502-44-person364">
                  Levi 
                  Joseph 
               <interp inst="t17640502-44-person364" type="surname" value="Joseph"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-44-person364" type="given" value="Levi"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-44-person364" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was at the vestry, and heard Lazarus Barnard's complaint. I said the prisoner had offered them to me to sell: he sent me to buy them: I went and bought them of the prisoner at the bar. (Produced and deposed to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I had these goods of another person to sell for him.</p>
               <p>He called 
               <persName id="t17640502-44-person365">
                  Solomon 
                  Hart 
               <interp inst="t17640502-44-person365" type="surname" value="Hart"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-44-person365" type="given" value="Solomon"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-44-person365" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , 
               <persName id="t17640502-44-person366">
                  Abraham 
                  Rodrega 
               <interp inst="t17640502-44-person366" type="surname" value="Rodrega"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-44-person366" type="given" value="Abraham"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-44-person366" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , and 
               <persName id="t17640502-44-person367">
                  Henry 
                  Symonds 
               <interp inst="t17640502-44-person367" type="surname" value="Symonds"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-44-person367" type="given" value="Henry"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-44-person367" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            ; who gave him a good character.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17640502-44-verdict248" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17640502-44-verdict248" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs>. <rs id="t17640502-44-punish249" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17640502-44-punish249" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640502-44-defend360 t17640502-44-punish249"></join>
               T
            </rs>. </p>
            </div1>
